<% content_for :title do %>Lasting Power of Attorney - Service dashboard - GOV.UK<% end %>

<% @js_config = {
  "controller" => "lpa/controllers/overview",
	"service-name" => service_name,
} %>

<header>
  <h1>
      <span class="strapline">Service dashboard</span>
      Lasting Power of Attorney
  </h1>
  <p class="explanatory">Figures for the service to make a <strong>lasting power of attorney (<abbr title="lasting power of attorney">LPA</abbr>)</strong> â€“ a legal document that lets you appoint someone, known as an 'attorney', to make decisions on your behalf. Figures include applications made via both digital and non-digital channels.</p>
</header>

<% if Rails.application.config.feature_toggles[:lpa_dashboard_application_method] %>
<section class="graph graph-with-labels application-method-over-time">
  <h1>Completed applications</h1>
  <aside class='more-info'>
    <span class='more-info-link'>more info</span>
    <ul>
      <li>Data source: Office of the Public Guardian</li>
      <li>Non-digital applications include all applications made using the traditional paper based forms.</li>
      <li>Digital applications include applications created using the Lasting Power of Attorney digital service.</li>
      <li>Applications are counted at point of receipt.</li>
    </ul>
  </aside>
  <h2><span class="group0">Non-digital</span> and <span class="group1">digital</span> applications over time</h2>
  <figure class="graph" id="application-method-over-time"></figure>
</section>
<% end %>

<% if Rails.application.config.feature_toggles[:lpa_dashboard_completion_rate] %>
<section class="graph single-decker-graph">
  <h1>Completion rate</h1>
  <aside class='more-info'>
    <span class='more-info-link'>more info</span>
    <ul>
      <li>Data source: Google Analytics</li>
      <li><a href="/service-manual/measurement/completion-rate.html" rel="external" target="_blank">Completion rate</a> measures the proportion of people who started an application and were able to complete it.</li>
      <li>It is calculated as percentage of unique visitors who arrived at the final page of the digital service out of those who arrived at the 'Choose LPA type' page.</li>
      <li>After using the digital service, users have further offline steps to complete, which this does not measure.</li>
    </ul>
  </aside>
  <h2>Proportion of people who completed both parts of the digital service, 'Make an LPA' and 'Register an LPA'</h2>
  <p id="lpa-completion-selected" class="impact-number"></p>
  <figure class="graph timeseries-graph" id="lpa-completion"></figure>
</section>
<% end %>

<% if Rails.application.config.feature_toggles[:lpa_conversion_funnel] %>
<section class="graph">
  <h1>Stages of making an <abbr title="lasting power of attorney">LPA</abbr></h1>
  <aside class='more-info'>
    <span class='more-info-link'>more info</span>
    <ul>
      <li>Data source: Google Analytics</li>
      <li>Stages are in the order a user would see them as they progress through the transaction.</li>
      <li>Shows significant stages only.</li>
      <li>Number of users is measured using the count of unique events from each stage.</li>
    </ul>
  </aside>
  <h2>Number of users at stages a user goes through whilst making an <abbr title="lasting power of attorney">LPA</abbr>. Some stages may be repeated or returned to, as indicated by higher numbers.</h2>
  <figure class="graph conversion-graph" id="lpa-conversion-graph"></figure>
</section>
<% end %>

<section class="help-usage">
  <h1>Help usage</h1>
  <aside class='more-info'>
    <span class='more-info-link'>more info</span>
    <ul>
      <li>Data source: Google Analytics</li>
      <li>Help buttons are available to assist users as they complete the transaction.</li>
      <li>Help usage counts the number of unique visitors who clicked on each help button.</li>
    </ul>
  <h2>How often help buttons in the transaction were used last week</h2>
  </aside>
  <article class="help-usage-table"></article>
</section>


<%= render(partial: "common/modules/availability") if Rails.application.config.feature_toggles[:show_lpa_availability] %>
